title: UGA targets elite, out-of-state safety
text:
Manage UGA targets elite, out-of-state safety Georgia has tossed its hat into the ring for one of the nation's best and he's from the same place as a pair of 2017 Bulldog signees. Slot to Georgia Links 
Georgia reached up into Philadelphia, Pa. and signed a pair of four-star prospects in 2017 and it's looking to grab another in the 2018 class. Imhotep Institute safety Isheem Young tweeted from his personal account Monday evening that the Bulldogs are the latest to offer. 
Running back D'Andre Swift and wide receiver Mark Webb are both from Philadelphia and will report to Athens this June after signing earlier this month. They became the first players from the Keystone State to sign with UGA since Musa Smith in 2000. Not a member? For a limited time, buy one month of Dawgs247 VIP, get two months FREE! 
Young is considered as one of the top players in the country, ranking No. 56 overall and as the sixth safety in the nation according to the industry-generated 247Sports Composite. He's also the No. 3 prospect in Pennsylvania. 
The six predictions in Young's 247Sports Crystal Ball, however, indicate that the Bulldogs have their work cut out for them. Penn State is the leader with 67 percent, followed by Florida State with 33 percent.
